Galvanize will host the Unearthed San Francisco hackathon event next weekend (9/23/16 - 9/25/16) at its San Francisco campus. Unearthed is a 54 hour hackathon event featuring challenges and data from global mining and resources companies. Those challenges and datasets are current industry problems that have been sourced from different corners of the world and are million and billion dollar projects. This means that even the smallest amount of improvement that a participant at the Unearthed hackathon can make on a particular challenge/dataset will have massive efficiency gains. Challenge providers BHP Billiton and Caterpillar are looking for the brightest young innovators and entrepreneurs to come in and solve their challenges. To put it into perspective, BHP Billiton operates the world’s largest private heavy haul network in the world, each iron ore train on average contains over 230 ore cars carrying 34+ thousand tons of ore worth over $2 million dollars. Every minute of lost time is equivalent to over $28,000. 

Unearthed is looking to invite software developers and data scientists to its hackathon event to build solutions to those challenges. This is an opportunity like no other and Unearthed is pleased to offer 15 Galvanize alumni with free tickets to #UnearthedSF.
All you need to do is go to the registration page <http://bit.ly/UESF16> and use the code GalvanizeDS100 to get your free ticket.
This code is limited to the first 15 people that get in, so don’t miss out!

attachments.title: Unearthed San Francisco 2016
attachments.text: Unearthed is a 54-hour open innovation Hackathon featuring real challenges and data from the resources sector. Software developers, data scientists, engineers, designers, entrepreneurs and industry insiders are invited to develop prototype technology solutions to industry challenges. Participants at Unearthed will have the unique opportunity to work on data and build improved solutions that tackle the challenges on offer.Participants at #UnearthedSF will work in teams, come together over the course of a weekend and build technologies for the future in the resources and mining sectors. There are two challenges on offer at #UnearthedSF from BHP Billiton and Caterpillar. Visit <http://portal.unearthed.solutions> and click through to the San Francisco event to view the challenges. Teams are required to select one challenge for the weekend at Unearthed.Participants retain 100% of the Intellectual Proprty (IP) that they generate at Unearthed, providing the opportunity to continue post-event development, combine your projects with current work and even go as far as to create startups or commercialise technologies.Visit the unearthed.solutions website for full details about the event, the challenges, past results, and our supporters. Quick Schedule breakdown isFriday - 5:00pm Event Opens, 12:00PM event closeSaturday - 8:00am Event Reopens, 12:00PM event closeSunday - 8:00am Event Reopens, 4pm Pitches Start, 7pm Awards, 9:00PM event ends.Cornerstone Supporters Caterpillar and BHP Billiton will host industry challenges alongside additional mining and resources companies from around the world. FAQ'sCan I come ready as a team? Can I participate as an individual? I don't have a team, but still wish to come along, can I do so?We recommend that you work as a team. We have found the most successful team size is between 3 to 4, but teams can be more or less. If you don’t have a team then we’ll help you to form one at the info session or on the opening evening.When is the Info Session? A live streamed Info Session will be held approximately one week before Unearthed San Francisco 2016. The Unearthed crew will live stream the Info Session from Australia. Exact details will be announced closer to the event  via email, social media and on our website. Follow Unearthed on social media links to be kept informed.I won’t be able to make it for the full weekend, can I still come? If you are unable to make one of the days/nights, that’s OK. Just let us know or let your team members know beforehand. If you haven’t formed a team yet and cannot make the Friday night, drop us an email and we’ll try to put you in a team so that you’re ready on Saturday.What is the cost? And what does it involve?Innovator tickets are for the full weekend. This includes breakfast, lunch, dinner, coffees and drinks all weekend! It also includes industry mentoring and tech startup experts.When will the challenges be released? Can we start working earlier?Descriptions of the challenges will be released the week before the event. All code, design and assets must be created during the hackathon or be freely available to the public (open source). Attend the info session prior to the hackathon in order to get prepared.Who owns what we make at the event?All teams retain full ownership of what is created during the event, barring any prior agreements you might have with employers, universities, etc... You own 100% of the IP that you create.What are the types of skills I need to have in my team to succeed at Unearthed? Unearthed recommends that your team consist of a mix of individuals who each bring different skills to the event. At least one programmer/developer (open source), a data scientist (number cruncher), a designer (can make the tech look amazing) and perhaps an entrepreneur with a business mind who can think of your project in terms of its value and market position. Other backgrounds include engineering and geology, depending on the challenge that your team selects at the event.

attachments.title: Pars Generation+ Career Fair
attachments.text: Please join Pars Generation+ 1st Career Fair on Thursday September 15, 2016 from 1pm - 6pm in San Francisco at Galvanize to to meet talent for your company, meet hiring managers and recruiters of companies who are hiring.   THANK YOU to our partner Galvanize for hosting us at their beautiful Venue!   About Pars Generation+:The goal of Pars Generation+ is simple but multi-faceted. Broadly, we want to be the glue that brings our community together both as individuals and as organizations. On the ground, we want to provide the younger generation of Iranians, both immigrant and American-born, with career mentors, peer mentors, and career opportunities. We also want to provide this younger generation opportunities to connect with their Iranian culture and heritage. In short, our mission is to “Act as a catalyst for social, cultural and economic integration of Iranians, and Persian speaking communities, to achieve their highest potential and to stay connected to their shared Iranian culture.” “Empowering The Next Generation Through Community, Career & Connection”    If you would like to get involved as a mentor, sponsor, partner please email us at <mailto:parsgenerationplus@parsequalitycenter.org|parsgenerationplus@parsequalitycenter.org> to receive more information.

attachments.title: Level Up: Building the Future as Engineers of Color
attachments.text: This panel explores the stories, experiences and personal journeys of women and men of color working as engineers in the tech world. The audience is open to all races and genders. We hope to inspire those who are trying to transition into a career in engineering, or are in the industry and seeking perspectives from other engineers and developers who not only overcome race and gender bias, but have also thrived.Moderator: Bianca St. LouisPanelists: To be announced soon!Sponsored by Galvanize and organized by Aniyia Williams, Founder of Tinsel and CODE2040 Entrepreneur-in-Residence (EIR), this is the first event of many to highlight the journey, opportunity, and community around being Black and Latino/a in tech. The goal of this event series is to bring people of color in tech together with individuals and organizations who can help them “Level Up”.Whether you are already in the industry or looking for a way in, come out to build a network and hear new perspectives. Also, If you are an ally or looking to hire a diverse team of engineers, we encourage you to come and connect with the community!(Photo Credit: #WOCinTech Chat)
